<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-89-0857 </DOCNO><TEXT>This book is a review of renewable energy policies of six leading manufacturingnations: U.S., Japan, Germany, Israel, France, and Denmark, which coversthe role of renewable energy in national energy policy, production policyand international cooperation and trade policy, and domestic renewableenergy consumption incentives and policies. The report includes ten casestudies of international renewable energy transactions which were accomplishedwith the assistance of one or more of the programs described above. Eightexporting countries, nine market countries involved in six renewableenergy technologies are analyzed in this authoritative study.</TEXT></DOC>